%N A089918 (n+1)*a(n) equals the (n+1)-th term of the n-th binomial transform of this sequence.
%H A089918 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A089918/b089918.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..292</a>
%F A089918 From _Seiichi Manyama_, Mar 03 2026: (Start)
%F A089918 a(0) = 1; a(n) = Sum_{k=1..n} n^(k-1) * binomial(n,k) * a(n-k).
%F A089918 a(0) = 1; a(n) = n! * [x^n] (1/n) * exp(n*x) * Sum_{k=0..n-1} a(k)*x^k/k!. (End)
%e A089918 Note the diagonal {(n+1)*a(n)} in array of iterated binomial transforms of this sequence:
